    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-01-04T01:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-01-04T01:30:00-05:00" n="210"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d210">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">501.<gloss target="#t_BC1">BC</gloss>/1–448:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Pakistan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lewis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret   immediate</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Karachi</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-01-04T12:00:00+05:30"
                            >January 4, 1948—noon</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6. Liaquat Ali Khan has telegraphed<note n="1" xml:id="d210fn1">For text of
                        telegram dated January 3, see United Nations, <hi rend="italic">Official
                            Records of the Security Council, Third Year, Nos. 1–15</hi>, p. 4.
                        Hereafter cited as <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss>, <hi rend="italic">3rd
                            yr., Nos</hi>.</note> Secretary General UN stating <gloss
                        target="#t_GOP1">GOP</gloss> has not yet seen India’s references which Delhi
                    sent Karachi <pb facs="0284" n="270" xml:id="pg_270"/> in undecipherable code
                    but text expected by air today, impossible prepare case and place it before
                        <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> by sixth, that Foreign Minister Sir
                    Zafrullah Khan will be sent as Pakistan’s chief delegate to present case before
                        <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> but is now in Burma to represent Pakistan
                    in Burma independence celebrations. Prime Minister requests stay of proceedings
                    “to give us reasonable time to prepare our case and to despatch our delegation”.
                        Ispahani<note n="2" xml:id="d210fn2">Mirza Abol Hassan Ispahani, Ambassador
                        of Pakistan in the United States.</note> directed proceed New York and
                    remain in touch with Secretary General (<gloss target="#t_mytel1">mytel</gloss>
                    5, January 3).<note n="3" xml:id="d210fn3">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Ikramullah has expressed <gloss target="#t_GOP1">GOP</gloss>’s hope US Govt will
                    use its influence effect stay in proceedings <gloss target="#t_Deptel1"
                        >Deptel</gloss> 1, January 1 pending preparation case and despatch of
                    representative.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lewis</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
